text: WMYQ (92.7 FM) is a radio station licensed to serve the community of Moorhead, Mississippi, and broadcasting to the Moorhead/Greenwood area. The station is owned by Delta Radio Network, through licensee Contemporary Communications LLC. It airs a country music format. The station was assigned the WMYQ call letters by the Federal Communications Commission on August 17, 2016. In 2018, the station hired David Mueller, performing under the name Stonewall Jackson, who lost a civil lawsuit for sexual assault against Taylor Swift.
